// Adversarial: Nova Lance is a multi-stage evolution chip that fires a nested 3-level trigger
// chain: PerfectBumped → Impacted(Cell) → PiercingBeam. AlwaysPerfect input guarantees a
// perfect bump every breaker contact, so the outer PerfectBumped trigger fires at maximum rate.
// Each perfect bump arms the Impacted(Cell) listener, which then fires PiercingBeam on the
// next cell impact — meaning every cell impact following a perfect bump generates a full beam
// sweep. Dense layout maximises cell impacts per frame, so multiple beams can be active
// simultaneously across different bolt trajectories. The adversarial risk: if the intermediate
// Impacted(Cell) listener accumulates without being consumed (the PerfectBumped arm fires but
// no cell impact follows before the next PerfectBumped), duplicate arm registrations stack up
// and NoEntityLeaks fires for orphaned listener entities. BoltInBounds catches any bolt whose
// trajectory is corrupted by simultaneous beam sweeps that modify cell positions mid-frame.
// NoNaN guards against position NaN from a beam sweep over a cell destroyed by a simultaneous
// earlier beam in the same frame. BoltSpeedAccurate catches speed corruption from overlapping
// PiercingBeam damage multiplier applications.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Perfect(AlwaysPerfect),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltCountReasonable, BoltInBounds, BoltSpeedAccurate, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 2311,
    chip_selections: ["Nova Lance"],
)
